# NAME: Apple Services
# AUTHOR: Steven
# UPDATED: 2026-06-26
# DESCRIPTION: Shadowrocket rule-set for Apple services — App Store, iCloud,
#              Music, TV+, Siri, Maps, FaceTime, iMessage, APNs, Software Updates.
#              Uses DOMAIN-SUFFIX so all subdomains are matched automatically.

# ── Apple Core ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Covers: App Store, iMessage, FaceTime, Siri, Maps, Pay, Apple ID,
#         Software Updates, Developer tools, Sign in with Apple, TestFlight
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,apple.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,apple.co
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,apple.news

# ── iCloud ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Drive, Photos, Keychain, Backup, Mail, Notes, iCloud Private Relay
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,icloud.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,icloud-content.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,apple-dns.net

# ── App Store & iTunes Store ───────────────────────────────────────────
# App downloads, media previews, purchase receipts, in-app content
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,mzstatic.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,itunes.com

# ── CDN & Images ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# App icons, screenshots, Apple Music artwork, Maps tiles
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,aaplimg.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,cdn-apple.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,apple-mapkit.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,appleiphonecell.com

# ── APNs — Apple Push Notification Service (IP-based) ──────────────────
# domain push.apple.com is caught by DOMAIN-SUFFIX,apple.com above.
# The IP-CIDR rules cover direct-IP connections some devices make to APNs
# data centres (hardcoded within Apple's 17.0.0.0/8 allocation).

# IPv4
IP-CIDR,17.57.144.0/22,no-resolve
IP-CIDR,17.57.148.0/22,no-resolve
IP-CIDR,17.172.228.0/22,no-resolve
IP-CIDR,17.188.20.0/23,no-resolve
IP-CIDR,17.188.128.0/18,no-resolve
IP-CIDR,17.249.60.0/22,no-resolve

# IPv6
IP-CIDR6,2620:149:a44::/48,no-resolve
IP-CIDR6,2403:300:a42::/48,no-resolve
IP-CIDR6,2403:300:a51::/48,no-resolve
IP-CIDR6,2a01:b740:a42::/48,no-resolve
